(
<figureCitation id="1371FDBF99218553E88FFC4ED5B5F3A5" box="[159,228,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1172,1197]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,179,1141]" captionTargetId="figure@55.[151,1435,166,1153]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 8. Selected Portuguese habitats of dolichopodid species. A. 4 km SSW of Manteigas, Serra da Estrela, river Zêzere, May 2014 (Orthoceratium sabulosum); B. Mouriscas, Tejo river, March 2011 (Medetera feminina); C. Salreu, Ria de Aveiro, June 2010 (Dolichopus andalusiacus, Chrysotus gramineus); D. Santa Luzia, April 2011 (Medetera ambigua); E. Santa Margarida da Coutada, March 2011 (Syntormon pallipes); F. São Marcos da Serra, Ribeira de Odelouca, September 2010 (Acropsilus niger, Hercostomus verbekei, Sybistroma dufourii); G. detail of same location; H. Tornada, Paul de Tornada, July 2010 (Poecilobothrus bigoti, Poecilobothrus principalis); I. detail of same location, with yellow pan trap." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3357639/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Figs 8</figureCitation>
F–G)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350B2B199218553E887FC06D73EF485" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99218553E887FC06D77CF47D" blockId="39.[151,1437,1016,1259]" box="[151,557,1016,1043]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553E887FC06D743F47D" bold="true" box="[151,530,1016,1043]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99218553E8D7FBE3D729F435" blockId="39.[151,1437,1016,1259]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553E8D7FBE3D430F459" bold="true" box="[199,353,1052,1079]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to the western part of Europe (incl. the Mediterranean region); also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99218553ED7DFBE2D582F435" name="Portugal" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three provinces, all over the country.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99218553E8D7FB9AD1CCF4CD" blockId="39.[151,1437,1016,1259]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553E8D7FB9AD47DF411" bold="true" box="[199,300,1125,1151]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ecology.</emphasis>
Similar distribution over macrohabitat categories as previous species. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999218553ED91FB99D5A7F4CD" authorityName="Pollet" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbekei">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553ED91FB99D5A7F4CD" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">H. verbekei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly found in marshlands and reedmarshes in the coastal region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB99218553EC1AFB76D1C1F4CD" author="Pollet, M." box="[1034,1168,1161,1187]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="101 - 109" refId="ref34232" refString="Pollet, M. (1993) Morphological and ecological characterization of Hercostomus (Hercostomus) plagiatus and a sibling species, H. verbekei sp. n. (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Zoologica Scripta, 22 (1), 101 - 109. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1993. tb 00344. x" type="journal article" year="1993">Pollet 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99218553E8D7FB53D714F4A9" blockId="39.[151,1437,1016,1259]" box="[199,581,1196,1223]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553E8D7FB53D400F4A9" bold="true" box="[199,337,1196,1223]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
3.4 (rare). Rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99218553E8D7FB2FD73EF485" blockId="39.[151,1437,1016,1259]" box="[199,623,1232,1259]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899218553E8D7FB2FD4D3F485" bold="true" box="[199,386,1232,1259]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Activity period.</emphasis>
September–October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
